sbml2modelica.sbmlabstraction

Class FunctionAbstractionManager

  • java.lang.Object
    • sbml2modelica.sbmlabstraction.FunctionAbstractionManager

  • public class FunctionAbstractionManager
extends java.lang.Object
    A FunctionAbstractionManager provides functionalities for generation of AbstractFunctions in an AbstractModel from the informations provided by a SBML Model.
    The FunctionAbstractionManager works under the assumption that the SBML Model has been pre-processed with a ModelPreprocessingManager.
    Author:
    Maggioli Filippo

      • FunctionAbstractionManager

        FunctionAbstractionManager(AbstractModel model,
                           org.sbml.jsbml.Model sbmlmodel)
                    throws NullAbstractModelException,
                           NullSBMLModelException
        Constructor initializes the FunctionAbstractionManager with the given AbstractModel and SBML Model.
        If one between the two inputs is null, then a proper exception is thrown.
        Parameters:
        model - The AbstractModel where the informations must be stored.
        sbmlmodel - The SBML Model from which the informations are retrieved.
        Throws:
        NullAbstractModelException - When model == null.
        NullSBMLModelException - When sbmlmodel == null.

        private void generateFunctionArguments(AbstractFunction af,
                                       org.sbml.jsbml.FunctionDefinition fd)
        This method generates the list of Strings that represents the vector of arguments of the given AbstractFunction.

        fd - The SBML Function that contains the informations.
